The evidence with the title 'Why won't Americans listen to Alan Simpson and Erskine Bowles ... ' says Feb 28, 2013  ... Their deliberations yielded a plan that reduced the federal deficit by $ 4 trillion over 10 years , mainly by cutting Medicare, Medicaid, Social Security, and the military budget ; raising taxes mostly on high earners; and curtailing popular-but- expensive tax breaks such as the one for home mortgage interest. 
